{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-14338].
  {panel}

Instances who add Bitbucket to their OnDemand account see a new Bitbucket option in their application navigator.

When they deactivate Bitbucket, their account remains linked from the application navigator. This is unacceptable for customers - especially after haven mistakenly added Bitbucket through their OnDemand account when they were simply trying to integrate an existing Bitbucket account with their OnDemand account.  They would now have two links, and have to try to educate their users on which to click.

Create New user in JIRA. The user is actually getting a 403 (plan exceeded) message in the JIRA logs. See screenshot. 

{code}
2013-09-30 18:08:40.298259500 Response code 403
2013-09-30 18:08:40.299027500 2013-09-30 18:08:40,298 TP-Processor2 WARN sysadmin 1088x23547x1 1vb1v7k 12.250.157.102,131.103.27.17 /rest/bitbucket/1.0/defaultgroups [plugins.dvcs.rest.RootResource] Failed to get groups for organization vivint. Cause message is com.atlassian.jira.plugins.dvcs.spi.bitbucket.clientlibrary.request.BitbucketRequestException$Forbidden_403
{code}

Ideally we can provide that feedback to the JIRA admin in a dialog box message.

Currently the Bitbucket connector bundles the AJS library.

If a resource in the plugin needs AJS, it should set a dependency to it like this (in its webresource module):
{noformat}
<dependency>com.atlassian.auiplugin:ajs</dependency>
{noformat}

On BitBucketTabPanel.java (ln 425)
{code}
 // Catches invalid or removed BitBucket IDs
            }catch (JSONException e){
                //e.printStackTrace();
                return "";
            }
{code}

This makes it very difficult to debug what is happening on a customer's instance if they are using their own private repos.

If a commit has a quote such as:

{quote}ABC-123 #comment This should actually fix it, but I can't fully verify until ABC-456 is fixed.{quote}

It will be truncated at the point that an issue key is next mentioned, so it will show up as
{quote}This should actually fix it, but I can't fully verify until{quote}

It should display the full comment on ABC-123.

